<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-47-1183 </DOCNO><TEXT>Osteoscintiscanning with /sup 99m/Tc-pyrophosphate is used for examinationof 19 patients from 1 to 15 years with multiple skeleton lesions. Radionuclidediagnosis data are compared with results of roentgenography. Sensitivityof radionuclide diagnosis of multiple skeleton lesions consisted 93%,of roentgenological - 30.2%. Use of osteoscintiscanning with /sup 99m/Tc-pyrophosphateincreases the efficiency of diagnosis of multiple skeleton tumors inchildren by 62.8%.</TEXT></DOC>